version: 1
display_name: PHTN-50-000221 - The Photon operating system must configure Secure Shell (SSH) to restrict LoginGraceTime.
global_description: |-
  By default, SSH unauthenticated connections are left open for two minutes before being closed. This setting is too permissive as no legitimate login would need such an amount of time to complete a login. Quickly terminating idle or incomplete login attempts will free up resources and reduce the exposure any partial logon attempts may create.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - PHTN-50-000221
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227
  cci:
    - CCI-000366
  nist:
    - CM-6 b
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_photon_5:
    type: custom
    desc: The Photon operating system must configure Secure Shell (SSH) to restrict LoginGraceTime.
    control_id: PHTN-50-000221
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      At the command line, run the following command to verify the running configuration of sshd:

      # sshd -T|&grep -i LoginGraceTime

      Example result:

      logingracetime 30

      If "LoginGraceTime" is not set to "30", this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      By default, SSH unauthenticated connections are left open for two minutes before being closed. This setting is too permissive as no legitimate login would need such an amount of time to complete a login. Quickly terminating idle or incomplete login attempts will free up resources and reduce the exposure any partial logon attempts may create.
    remediation: |-
      Navigate to and open:

      /etc/ssh/sshd_config

      Ensure the "LoginGraceTime" line is uncommented and set to the following:

      LoginGraceTime 30

      At the command line, run the following command:

      # systemctl restart sshd.service
